lead_paragraph: Macy’s Thanksgiving Day Parade (Thursday) Sometimes even balloons need a makeover. Snoopy, Woodstock and SpongeBob SquarePants will be sporting new looks as they float along with the other balloon characters, bands, clowns and marchers that are part of this year’s 87th holiday spectacle.

abstract: Two exhibitions now in New York have much to say about the imbalance of money and taste in the Gilded Age of the late 1800s.
snippet: Two exhibitions now in New York have much to say about the imbalance of money and taste in the Gilded Age of the late 1800s.
lead_paragraph: The staggering sums spent on art at last week’s auctions were interpreted by dealers and critics alike as evidence of a new Gilded Age. At such a moment, it may be useful to take a hard look at the old one, the late-19th-century period defined by the aggressive buying sprees of a few newly minted industrialists.

abstract: Illinois was hit especially hard by tornadoes that tore through the Midwest on Sunday, killing at least six people and leaving hundreds of thousands without power.
snippet: Illinois was hit especially hard by tornadoes that tore through the Midwest on Sunday, killing at least six people and leaving hundreds of thousands without power.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Ill. — As the sky went black and sirens wailed, Ella and Phil Bolam lay together in a bedroom closet, pillows covering their heads, as the storm passed and “the house went away,” Ms. Bolam said.

abstract: A guide to a range of cultural events in New York, including discussions, film screenings and exhibitions.
snippet: A guide to a range of cultural events in New York, including discussions, film screenings and exhibitions.
lead_paragraph: Iranian New Wave 1960s-1970s Film Series (through next Friday) When his documentaries about life in Iran under the pro-Western shah, Mohammad Reza Pahlavi, focused too much on the poverty he saw, Kamran Shirdel — originally commissioned by the government to make these films — was expelled, and forced to leave some work behind. Four of his short films — several completed after the Islamic Revolution of 1979 — will be screened on Wednesday, starting at 6:30 p.m., at Asia Society, 725 Park Avenue, at 70th Street.

abstract: For seven weeks, tenants in a storefront on Delancey Street will range from a syringe-exchange program for homeless transients to an online community of knitters.
snippet: For seven weeks, tenants in a storefront on Delancey Street will range from a syringe-exchange program for homeless transients to an online community of knitters.
lead_paragraph: Eric Ho watches the boom on the Lower East Side, the torrent of new restaurants and boutiques opening, and sees something different. He sees Detroit. Specifically, walking the neighborhood last spring, he saw vacant storefronts — more than 200 of them in the area east of the Bowery and south of 14th Street.

abstract: Penny Arcade, a longtime downtown performance artist and archivist, takes on a role in “The Mutilated,” a Tennessee Williams play.
snippet: Penny Arcade, a longtime downtown performance artist and archivist, takes on a role in “The Mutilated,” a Tennessee Williams play.
lead_paragraph: In 1967, the same year that the playwright Tennessee Williams found himself in the depths of substance abuse, depression and critical failure, a short, busty, outspoken 17-year-old named Susana Ventura completed her tenure in reform school and ran away from working-class New Britain, Conn. She moved to downtown Manhattan, was sheltered by drag queens and fell under the tutelage of gay artists including Andy Warhol; the filmmaker and performance artist Jack Smith; and John Vaccaro, founder of the avant-garde Play-House of the Ridiculous theater group.

lead_paragraph: Village Halloween Parade and Costume Ball (Thursday) Barring any disastrous weather — last year’s hurricane put an end to many holiday plans — Halloween celebrations will be in full swing. Billed as the “Hallelujah Halloween Revival,” the Village Halloween Parade will proceed up Avenue of the Americas, from Spring Street to 16th Street, at 7 p.m.
